{{use American English|date=May 2015}} {{use mdy dates|date=May 2015}} {{infobox company | name = MDVIP | logo = | caption = | type = [[Privately held company]] | foundation = {{Start date and age|2000}} | founder = | hq_location_city = [[Boca Raton, Florida|Boca Raton]], [[Florida]] | hq_location_country = United States | coordinates = | area_served = 45 states and the [[District of Columbia]] | key_people = | industry = Health care | services = [[Primary care|Primary-care medicine]] | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | num_employees = | parent = [[Leonard Green & Partners]] | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{url|mdvip.com}} }}
'''MDVIP''' is an American company, headquartered in [[Boca Raton, Florida|Boca Raton]], [[Florida]], that operates a network of physicians. The company's [[physician]]s practice [[preventive medicine]] and personalized [[Primary care|primary-care medicine]].
The national network consists of 900 physicians serving over 280,000 patients in 45 states and the District of Columbia. Each physician cares for up to 600 patients as opposed to the average 2,500-3,500 patients in a traditional primary-care practice. MDVIP patients receive a [[Physical examination|comprehensive physical examination]] and follow-up wellness plan as well as electronic medical records and a personalized patient portal with focus on diet, exercise, doctor communication and more. The company states that additional patient benefits include [[acute care|acute-care]] visits, same or next-day availability, on-time appointments, 24/7 physician availability, and enhanced coordination of specialty care.<ref>[https://www.mdvip.com/patients/benefits "MDVIP Patient Advantages"].</ref>
==History== Founded in Boca Raton in 2000, in June 2014, growth-equity investor [[Summit Partners]] acquired the company from [[Procter & Gamble Company]].<ref>[http://www.themiddlemarket.com/news/2/summit-partners-buys-mdvip-from-p-g-249552-1.html].</ref> In November 2017, Leonard Green & Partners acquired majority ownership. <ref>[https://www.mdvip.com/leonard-green-partners-acquires-majority-ownership-mdvip-summit-partners].</ref>
==Business model== To supplement insurance reimbursements, MDVIP physicians charge patients an annual fee between $1,650 and $2,200 per year.<ref>[https://www.mdvip.com/patients/benefits].</ref> In addition to this annual fee, patients are responsible for applicable co-pays and co-insurance, and maintain primary-care [[Health insurance|insurance]] coverage including [[Medicare (United States)|Medicare]].<ref>[https://archive.is/20100818014513/http://www.mdvip.com/patient/insurancemedicare.aspx MDVIP Insurance and Medicare].</ref><ref>[http://articles.boston.com/2011-04-17/business/29428534_1_concierge-medicine-mdvip-boutique-practices]{{dead link|date=May 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}. [[Boston.com]].</ref> In contrast to the [[Concierge medicine#Concierge medicine vs. direct primary care|direct-care model]], this revenue format, often referenced as [[concierge medicine]], runs the risk of audit or penalty as Medicare and other private-insurance carriers cover a comprehensive wellness exam currently listed as part of the MDVIP package.<ref>[http://www.aarp.org/health/health-care-reform/info-07-2011/free-medicare-wellness-exam.html "What You Need to Know About the New, Free Medicare Checkup"]. [[AARP]].</ref>
MDVIP physicians are not directly employed by the company, instead they pay a [[Royalties|royalty]] or [[Franchise fee|franchise]] fee of $500<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20111108211623/http://www.journalwatchdog.com/business/932-a-different-kind-of-doctoring "A Different Kind of Doctoring].</ref> per patient per year for services such as patient conversion, marketing, branding and other support.<ref>[https://forrestdirectpay.com/page/why-forrest-direct-pay "Forrest Direct Pay"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120402224259/https://forrestdirectpay.com/page/why-forrest-direct-pay |date=April 2, 2012 }}.</ref>
