'''Salivary gland atresia''' is congenital blockage or absence of the orifice of a major salivary gland duct or part of the duct itself.<ref name=Graamans2012>{{cite book|author1=Graamans K|author2=van den Hans A|title=Diagnosis of salivary gland disorders|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=urivBQAAQBAJ&pg=PT115|date=6 December 2012|publisher=Springer Science & Business Media|isbn=978-94-011-3608-2|page=115}}</ref>

It is a very rare condition.<ref name=Graamans2012 /><ref name=Chaudhary2012 /> The submandibular salivary gland duct is usually involved, having failed to cannulate during embryological development. The condition first becomes apparent in the first few days after birth where a submandibular swelling caused by a retention cyst is noticed.<ref name="Chaudhary2012">{{cite book|author1=Mayur Chaudhary M|author2=Chaudhary SD|title=Essentials of Pediatric Oral Pathology|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yCkArYWx_WIC&pg=PA304|date=1 April 2012|publisher=JP Medical Ltd|isbn=978-93-5025-374-8|page=304}}</ref>

